	 Alien$ 	 
		 
 One rather pervasive story concerning  Aliens  is how writer/director James Cameron convinced Brandywine Productions to green light the sequel. One version that has become popular lately is better known as ‘Alien$’, and the story—allegedly related by series producer Gordon Carroll—often goes this way: 
 “Cameron was young. He had just directed  Terminator . Cameron had called a meeting to discuss his “next project.” Everyone knew Cameron had written a treatment for  Alien 2  that nobody would touch because  Alien   was not a massive financial success.  Alien 2   was not on the table. We expected a professional pitch from Cameron, an outline